{"word":"ἆσσον","slug":"ἆσσον","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<el><b>ἆσσον</b></el> <br/><b><a href='S:Etymology'>Etym.</a> </b><a href='S:ἄγχι'><el>ἄγχι</el></a>\n<p/><i>nearer, very near</i>, <b><a href='S:Homer'>Hom.</a></b>: <a href='S:cum'>c.</a> <a href='S:genitive'>gen.</a>, <el>ἆσσον ἐμεῖο</el> <i>nearer</i> to me, <b><a href='S:Iliad'>Il.</a></b>; with a double <a href='S:Comparative'>comp.</a>, <el>μᾶλλον ἆσσον</el> <b><a href='S:Sophocles'>Soph.</a></b>:—hence, as a new <a href='S:Comparative'>comp.</a>, <el>ἀσσοτέρω</el>, with or without <a href='S:genitive'>gen.</a>, <b><a href='S:Odyssey'>Od.</a></b>; <a href='S:Superlative'>Sup.</a> <el>ἀσσοτάτω</el>, <b><a href='S:Anthology'>Anth.</a></b>; whence <a href='S:Adjective'>adj.</a> <el>ἀσσότατος</el> <b><a href='S:Anthology'>Anth.</a></b><p/>"}]}